Summertime in Northern Michigan

Our grandfather, “Pa,” was a very important person in our lives. We were lucky to have him for so long. After he passed on to heaven, our dad and uncles started a golf tournament in his honor with 24 cousins, brothers, and uncles. It’s one of the funnest days of the year and he would have loved every minute of it. Thanks @kevinpohle for capturing so many great moments.
#mynormalbrand #teambentley

We own a business, but we are brothers first. This is a video on our youngest (and favorite) brother. Every Friday, our nine siblings fly in from wherever they are (Nashville, New York, Dallas, etc) to watch him. Wins and losses mean very little when you compare it to the love you get from family. Football in the fall is the best.

We’ve been a fan of Andrew Arrabito and Half Face Blades for years now. We use his knives and are inspired by his story. We’ve always had so much appreciation for the men and women who protect our country, and as a Navy Seal, Andrew put it on the line for us every. single. day. He is the kind of guy you want on your team. 

As a custom knife maker, he designs blades that are usable, durable, purposeful, and then he chooses to make them beautiful. 

Getting to hang out at his production facility and his house that night for some moose and wagyu patty melts was a great time. Hope you enjoy seeing a bit of his Normal.
#mynormalbrand

Taking in the views.
#mynormalbrand #colorado

Opening our 10th brick and mortar store had us reflecting. Seven years ago to the day we opened our tenth store (in Franklin, TN), we bought this old camper for $600 out of some guy's yard in Illinois.  It was effectively our first "store." We would travel around with it and use it for pop-ups at churches, schools, trade shows, other stores, and random streets. It was a piece of junk. We fixed it up, and made it look pretty sharp. We were really proud of it. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Going to skip to the end real quick - it burned down to ashes due to an electrical fire.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Store No. 10 is a major improvement.

Our hometown of St. Louis has an incredible restaurant scene. We are lucky to have so many awesome chefs here. A few years ago we met Matt McGuire, the owner and visionary behind @louiedemun and @wrightsonwydown. And now we are regulars. The food is a ten, but Matt and his team bring much more than a great meal. You may walk in a guest, but you leave as family.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Matt knows what real teamwork means, and the value of working towards the same goal. In his words, “At the end of the night, it’s not about the food... It’s a generosity of spirit that makes people feel welcome.” The fact that the food is incredible just makes the experience better.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
We’re honored to have enjoyed a meal with Matt and learn more about his Normal.
#mynormalbrand
